    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Race-based affirmative action undermines meritocracy by substituting group identity for individual effort, creating a perception that opportunities are allocated based on birth rather than ability. This system inevitably encourages reverse discrimination, where disadvantaged groups are penalized for their successes while underrepresenting those who may face advantages due to socioeconomic luck. Ultimately, replacing blind casting with racial quotas does not ensure equal opportunity; instead, it fosters resentment and signals that a truly fair society should reward hard work above all else.",
